Homa Bay woman representative Gladys Wanga yesterday told political aspirants ODM nominations will be transparent.The county ODM chairperson wants aspirants to ignore a rumour that she is likely to influence the nominations.&ldquo;Any contestant should know the party constitution is clear that nomination certificates are issued by the National Elections Board on merit,&rdquo; Wanga said. Wanga told aspirants to understand she is also a contestant defending her seat, therefore, she has no mandate to influence the nomination.She said she is confident the party NEB will conduct fair nominations and certificates given to aspirants who deserve them. Wang urged aspirants to campaign peacefully and preach coexistence among residents during and after the elections.